Provenova is an open-core monorepo under two licenses. The per-directory
LICENSE files are authoritative:

  packages/ql-core/LICENSE      Apache License 2.0
  packages/ql-sdk/LICENSE       Apache License 2.0
  packages/ql-crawler/LICENSE   Apache License 2.0
  frameworks/                   Apache License 2.0 (compliance frameworks as data)
  server/LICENSE                Business Source License 1.1 (BUSL-1.1)

In short: the client SDK, provenance engine, schemas and crawler are open
source (Apache-2.0). The server is source-available (BUSL-1.1) — free to run,
production self-hosting included; the only reserved right is offering the
server to third parties as a competing hosted, managed, or embedded service.
Each server release converts to Apache-2.0 four years after it ships.

Plain-language guide with examples: https://provenova.net/docs/licensing
Commercial licensing: hi@ben.gy
